{{Gzdoomfeature}}
void '''ChangeActorRoll''' (int ''tid'', fixed ''angle'' [, bool ''interpolate''])

==Usage==
Sets the roll angle for the actors with the specified {{c|[[TID|tid]]}}. If ''tid'' is 0, it sets the roll angle for the activator of the script. Note that the function has a visual effect on models and player's view (when called for players) only. It has no effect on [[sprite]]s.

This function duplicates and extends on {{c|[[SetActorRoll]]}} by having the added option to interpolate the view.

===Parameters===
*''tid'': the {{c|tid}} of the actor.
*''angle'': the roll angle to set. This is a [[definitions|fixed point angle]] in the range of 0.0 to 1.0, with:
**{{c|0.25 → right}}
**{{c|0.5 → down}}
**{{c|0.75 → left}}
**{{c|1.0 → up}}
*''interpolate'': whether to interpolate the view or not. If {{c|true}}, the view is interpolated, otherwise it is not. Default is {{c|false}}, i.e. no interpolation.

